OL,6,F"In 2020, Frank entered the House of
OL,7,FLords as the Rt Hon the Lord Field of
OL,8,FBirkenhead, was appointed Member of
OL,9,Fthe Order of the Companions of Honour
OL,10,F(CH) in the 2022 New Year Honours and
OL,11,Fcontinued to serve on the boards of
OL,12,FCool Earth, Feeding Britain and the
OL,13,FFrank Field Education Trust.
OL,15,F"He will be mourned by admirers across
OL,16,Fpolitics but above all he will be
OL,17,Fgreatly missed by those lucky enough
OL,18,Fto have enjoyed his laughter and
OL,19,Ffriendship."
